  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Saturday. Grocery shopping with Sophia is never just \"grocery shopping.\" It is a full mission with rules, strategy, and occasional shouting.",
      "zh": "星期六。跟 Sophia 去買菜從來不會只是「買菜」，這是一場有規則、有策略、偶爾還會大聲喊叫的完整任務。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Rule one: we bring cash, because Sophia does not fully trust anything that is not paper money.",
      "zh": "第一條規則：一定要帶現金，因為 Sophia 對任何不是紙鈔的東西都不太信任。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Rule two: William is only allowed to touch things if he asks first, a rule he breaks approximately every ninety seconds.",
      "zh": "第二條規則：William 只有先問過才能碰東西，而這條規則他大概每九十秒就犯規一次。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We started in the fruit section, where Sophia squeezed every single peach like she was checking its heartbeat.",
      "zh": "我們先從水果區開始，Sophia 捏了每一顆桃子，好像在檢查它的心跳一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"This one is not ready,\" she said, putting back a pear. \"This one, also not ready.\" She rejected four pears before finally choosing one.",
      "zh": "「這顆還沒熟，」她說，把一顆梨子放回去，「這顆，也還沒熟。」她拒絕了四顆梨子才終於選中一顆。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We loaded the cart with mangoes, papayas, grapes, and one giant watermelon that William insisted on carrying by himself.",
      "zh": "我們把推車裝滿了芒果、木瓜、葡萄，還有一顆 William 堅持要自己搬的巨大西瓜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He lasted about four steps before Dad quietly took the watermelon back before it hit the floor.",
      "zh": "他撐了大概四步，爸爸就悄悄把西瓜接過去，免得它摔到地上。"
    },
    {
      "en": "In the vegetable section, Sophia grabbed cabbage, garlic, and corn, explaining the exact soup she was planning to make with each one.",
      "zh": "在蔬菜區，Sophia 拿了高麗菜、蒜頭和玉米，還一一解釋她打算用每樣東西煮什麼湯。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She also picked up a bag of soybeans and a block of tofu, telling William that protein does not always come from meat.",
      "zh": "她還拿了一袋大豆和一塊豆腐，跟 William 說蛋白質不是只能從肉裡來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, who only trusts food shaped like nuggets, looked at the tofu like it had personally insulted him.",
      "zh": "William 只信任長得像雞塊的食物，他看著那塊豆腐的表情，好像那塊豆腐親自羞辱了他一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At the meat counter, we bought pork, some beef, and a small package of seafood for Sophia's Sunday special.",
      "zh": "在肉品櫃檯，我們買了豬肉、一些牛肉，還有一小包海鮮，準備做 Sophia 星期天的拿手菜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William begged for a jar of jam, a bottle of ketchup, and two cans of cola, and somehow got all three into the cart when nobody was looking.",
      "zh": "William 一直吵著要一罐果醬、一瓶番茄醬，還有兩罐可樂，趁大家沒注意，居然三樣全塞進了推車裡。"
    },
    {
      "en": "We also grabbed a box of cereal, a bag of biscuits, a pack of buns, and a small tin of cocoa powder for cold mornings.",
      "zh": "我們還拿了一盒穀片、一包餅乾、一袋麵包卷，還有一小罐可可粉，準備留著寒冷的早晨喝。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"We are not buying pumpkin today,\" Sophia announced firmly, before anyone had even mentioned pumpkin.",
      "zh": "「我們今天不買南瓜，」Sophia 態度堅定地宣布，儘管根本沒有人提過南瓜這件事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Apparently she remembered last month's pumpkin disaster, which is a whole other diary entry I am not ready to write yet.",
      "zh": "顯然她還記得上個月的南瓜災難事件，那又是另一篇我還沒準備好寫的日記了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At the checkout counter, the cashier weighed our fruit, and the total cost made Sophia let out a long, dramatic sigh.",
      "zh": "在結帳櫃檯，收銀員秤了我們的水果，總金額讓 Sophia 發出一聲又長又誇張的嘆氣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Everything is so expensive now,\" she told the cashier, who has probably heard this exact complaint from every customer today.",
      "zh": "「現在什麼都好貴，」她跟收銀員說，那位收銀員大概今天已經聽過每個顧客都講過這句一模一樣的抱怨。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The cashier smiled politely and said the price on the bill was correct, no discount today, sorry.",
      "zh": "收銀員禮貌地笑了笑，說帳單上的價格沒有算錯，今天沒有折扣，抱歉。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia paid in cash, counted her change twice, and put every coin back into a small cloth purse she has owned since before I was born.",
      "zh": "Sophia 用現金付款，把找的錢數了兩次，然後把每一枚硬幣都放進一個她生我之前就有的小布錢包裡。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William tried to sneak a yam into the cart at the very last second, and somehow, this time, Sophia allowed it without an argument.",
      "zh": "William 在最後一秒試圖偷偷把一根地瓜塞進推車，這次不知道為什麼，Sophia 竟然沒吵就同意了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Back home, Sophia unpacked every bag herself, sorting fruit here, vegetables there, and snacks into a cabinet William is not tall enough to reach.",
      "zh": "回到家後，Sophia 親自把每個袋子都拆開整理，水果放這邊、蔬菜放那邊，零食則放進一個 William 還搆不到的櫃子裡。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By dinner, half the watermelon was already gone, mostly thanks to William and, admittedly, me.",
      "zh": "到晚餐時，半顆西瓜已經被吃光了，主要要感謝 William，還有，我承認，也要感謝我自己。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Lesson of the day: never underestimate how much a small grandmother with a cloth purse can carry, argue about, and win.",
      "zh": "今日心得：永遠不要小看一位拿著布錢包的嬌小阿嬤，她能扛多少東西、能吵贏多少場，還能贏下多少次。"
    }
  ],
